videos.description: In the first quarter, Auburn decides to go for it on fourth-and-2, with Chandler Cox running it in for a 3-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Auburn scores TD on fourth-and-2

videos.description: Oklahoma's Baker Mayfield rolls right and throws to Mark Andrews for a 13-yard touchdown in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Oklahoma ties game on Mayfield's 13-yard touchdown pass

videos.description: Oklahoma's Joe Mixon takes the handoff and rushes into the end zone for an easy 3-yard touchdown in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Mixon's 3-yard TD run gives Oklahoma the lead

videos.description: Oklahoma head coach Bob Stoops assesses his defense's first half performance, taking a 14-13 lead over Auburn into the locker room.
videos.headline: Stoops addresses second half adjustments for defense

videos.description: Kaylee Hartung provides an update on Auburn quarterback Sean White, who left the game in the first half and won't return due to an arm injury.
videos.headline: Auburn's White won't return to Sugar Bowl

videos.description: Oklahoma's Baker Mayfield tosses a bubble screen to Dede Westbrook who takes it seven yards for a touchdown.
videos.headline: Oklahoma's Westbrook takes the bubble screen to pay dirt

videos.description: Oklahoma's Dede Westbrook gets the ball in the backfield, fakes a pass and jukes out three Auburn defenders before running for a first down.
videos.headline: Westbrook turns botched play into first down

videos.description: Oklahoma's Joe Mixon continues his strong game with a 35-yard run into Auburn territory in the third quarter.
videos.headline: Mixon uses burst of speed for 35-yard gain

videos.description: Oklahoma's Samaje Perine takes the direct snap and cuts through the Auburn defense for a 2-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Perine cuts through traffic to extend Oklahoma's lead

videos.description: Joe Mixon takes the direct snap and heads for the pylon and originally gets ruled short of the end zone. After review, Mixon gets credited with a 4-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Mixon gets second TD on overturned call in OU's win

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Mixon's second TD pads Oklahoma's lead) 2017/01/02

videos.description: With Auburn driving in Oklahoma territory, Jeremy Johnson throws to the end zone, but his pass gets tipped and intercepted by the Sooners' Jordan Thomas.
videos.headline: Oklahoma's Jordan Thomas makes interception in end zone

videos.description: Samaje Perine rushes for 15 yards in the fourth quarter, giving him enough yards to pass Billy Sims on Oklahoma's all-time rushing list.
videos.headline: Perine becomes Oklahoma's all-time rushing leader in OU's win

videos.description: In what was his last game coaching the Sooners, Bob Stoops went out a winner as Oklahoma defeated Auburn 35-19 to win the Allstate Sugar Bowl.
videos.headline: Bob Stoops went out with Sugar Bowl win

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Sugar Bowl Oklahoma-Auburn Fulltime) 2017/01/02 ESHEET

videos.description: Oklahoma head coach Bob Stoops says that after a 1-2 start, his team was able to maintain confidence all the way through a victory in the Allstate Sugar Bowl.
videos.headline: Stoops says confidence was crucial for strong end to season

videos.description: Oklahoma's Baker Mayfield discusses the team overcoming a 1-2 start and putting in a solid effort against Auburn in the Allstate Sugar Bowl.
videos.headline: Mayfield proud of effort in Sugar Bowl victory

videos.description: Jesse Palmer breaks down Oklahoma's potent offense in  a 35-19 victory against Auburn in the Allstate Sugar Bowl.
videos.headline: Mayfield's ability to buy time crucial in Sugar Bowl win

videos.description: Sophomore Kamryn Pettway rushes for 101 yards in a Sugar Bowl loss to Oklahoma.
videos.headline: Tigers come up short against Sooners 35-19

videos.description: Oklahoma coach Bob Stoops joins Scott Van Pelt to recap the Sooners' win in the Allstate Sugar Bowl, building momentum after a 1-2 start and Samaje Perine becoming the team's all-time leading rusher.
videos.headline: Stoops glad the hard work paid off at Sugar Bowl

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Interview (Stoops glad the hard work paid off at Sugar Bowl) 2017/01/02 SVP SC ESHEET

videos.description: Auburn quarterback Sean White breaks his right arm on a 3-yard run in the first quarter against Oklahoma in the Allstate Sugar Bowl.
videos.headline: Auburn's White breaks arm on first-quarter hit

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Auburn's White breaks arm on first-quarter hit) 2017/01/02
